From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000006 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: NixOS module overlay <noreply@example.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Remove per-user storage quota for self-hosted deployments

Upstream zotero/dataserver enforces a 300 MB default storage quota per
user (Zotero_Storage::$defaultQuota), with per-user overrides stored in
zotero_master.storageAccounts. This is the same quota model as the
hosted zotero.org free tier — sensible there, pointless in a
self-hosted deployment where the operator already controls the storage
backend (minio / S3) and any disk-level limits live there, not in PHP.

Without this patch, every fresh user hits "out of space" errors from
the sync engine after ~300 MB of attachments and the only fix is to
manually INSERT a row into storageAccounts and bounce memcached, which
is a confusing first-run experience.

Bump the default to 10 TB (10485760 MB). This still goes through
getEffectiveUserQuota's per-user override path, so an operator who
wants to enforce real per-user limits can still do so via the
storageAccounts table — we're only changing what new/unconfigured
users get by default.
---
diff --git a/model/Storage.inc.php b/model/Storage.inc.php
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/model/Storage.inc.php
+++ b/model/Storage.inc.php
@@ -25,7 +25,9 @@
 */

 class Zotero_Storage {
-	public static $defaultQuota = 300;
+	// Self-hosted: default to effectively unlimited (10 TB in MB).
+	// Per-user overrides via storageAccounts still work as before.
+	public static $defaultQuota = 10485760;
 	public static $uploadQueueLimit = 10;
 	public static $uploadQueueTimeout = 300;
 	private static $s3PresignedRequestTTL = 3600;
